ry Warsaw seeking to find traces of the past. Written vividly and honestly, this unique tapestry of time and perspective not only stands out in the vast literature that discusses the Holocaust, but also appeals to anyone interested in the lasting impact of childhood trauma, as well as the human potential for resiliency.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aHolocaust survivorszCaliforniavBiography2DLC. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)zPolandvPersonal narratives2DLC. 0aJewish children in the HolocaustzPolandvBiography2DLC. 0aJewish children in the HolocaustzPolandzWarsaw2DLC. 0aJewish children in the HolocaustzPolandzWarsaw. 7aHISTORY / Holocaust.2bisacsh  aHolocaust Memoir, Childhood Trauma, Anti-semitism, Warsaw Ghetto, Warsaw Ghetto uprising, Poland history, WW2, Nazism, Survivor of the holocaust.1 aJanicka, Elżbieta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKwiet, Konrad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMasson, Jeffrey Moussaieff, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMasson, Simone, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMasson, Simone, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102354008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311143260108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2z978311117804208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2024 Part 2z978311133238340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/979888719222240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9798887192222423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9798887192222/original 